{{italic title}}
The '''''Abbey of the Holy Ghost''''' is a medieval [[prose]] [[allegory]], ca. 1350. The text is preserved in at least 26 manuscripts, often followed by the ''Charter of the Abbey of the Holy Ghost''. The text advises lay women on how to live a [[Contemplation|contemplative]] life outside a [[monastery]]; the companion ''Charter'' speaks of the [[Fall of Man|fall]] and [[Christian salvation|salvation]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Lagorio|first=V.M.|title=[[Lexikon des Mittelalters]]|publisher=Metzler|chapter=Abbey of the Holy Ghost|page=14}}</ref>

