'''Ma Jaya Sati Bhagavati''' (died April 14, 2012) was a spiritual teacher born to Jewish parents in [[Brooklyn]], United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcpalm.com/news/2012/apr/14/ma-jaya-bhagavati-spiritual-leader-of-kashi-dead/ |title=Ma Jaya Bhagavati, spiritual leader of Kashi, dead at 71 &#124; Photo Gallery |publisher=TCPalm.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-16}}</ref> Her outlook has been influenced by [[Jesus Christ]] and the [[Hindu]] saint [[Bhagawan Nityananda]]. She has also been informed by the teachings of [[Neem Karoli Baba]], [[Ramana Maharshi]], Narish Keit, and [[Shirdi Sai Baba]]. 

Ma Jaya Sati Bhagavati founded the Kashi Ashram, "an international interfaith community based on kindness, compassion and service", in [[Florida]] in 1976.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McCoy|first1=Terrence|title=Kashi Ashram: Claims of Rape, Child Abuse, and Kidnapping|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/news/kashi-ashram-claims-of-rape-child-abuse-and-kidnapping-6392115|accessdate=7 April 2017|work=Miami New Times|date=16 May 2013}}</ref>

