'''Ursula Coope''' is a British professor of ancient philosophy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-no2006021013/ |title=Coope, Ursula |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=November 22, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ndpr.nd.edu/news/time-for-aristotle/ |title=Book review |publisher=ND.edu |accessdate=November 22, 2017}}</ref> Since 2017, she holds the Professorship of Ancient Philosophy in the [[Faculty of Philosophy, University of Oxford]] and is a professorial fellow of [[Keble College, Oxford]]. Previously she was a tutorial fellow and professor of ancient philosophy at [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford]] and global distinguished professor at [[New York University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/people/ursula-coope|title=Ursula Coope|publisher=[[University of Oxford]]|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref>
In 1992, Coope graduated with a B.A. in [[philosophy, politics and economics]] at [[Corpus Christi College, Oxford]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/people/ursula-coope#tab-1-0|title=Ursula Coope {{!}} Faculty of Philosophy|website=www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-01-22}}</ref> In 1999 she was awarded her PhD in philosophy at the [[University of California, Berkeley]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/people/ursula-coope#tab-1-0|title=Ursula Coope {{!}} Faculty of Philosophy|website=www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-01-22}}</ref>
